Considerations for Direct Report Queries

You can visualize report data in any dashboard widget except for date and range widgets. Currently, tabular and summary report formats are supported.

When you change and save a report, those changes are visible in dashboards that use the report.

Direct report queries support faceting, binding, data source linking, and saved views. Targeted faceting using direct report queries isn’t supported.

Some report functionality isn’t available in a CRM Analytics dashboard, including record actions and column-level sorting. Also, direct report queries aren’t available in CRM Analytics notifications, subscriptions, and watchlists.

Formula fields in a report only appear with the Grouping view. Formula fields don’t appear in the Details and Summary views.
title: Considerations for Direct Report Queries in CRM Analytics
